Business Brief -- Franco-Nevada Mining Corp.:
   Company Agrees to Issue
   1 Million Special Warrants
If all the warrants are exercised, Franco-Nevada's common
shares outstanding would increase to about 14.2 million
shares from about 12.7 million shares currently. In trading
on the Toronto Stock Exchange yesterday, the shares closed at
C$27.50, off 12.5 Canadian cents.
   Franco-Nevada holds royalty interests in gold mines. It
said proceeds mostly will be used to acquire more royalty
interests.